- Fixed (2026-07-07): `Stations.handle_platform_state_change` used to only rename a new platform on the exact `waiting_for_starter_pack -> starter_pack_requested` transition. If the starter pack is manually pre-loaded into the silo before clicking "build new space platform", Factorio skips straight past `starter_pack_requested` to `starter_pack_on_the_way` (or later), so the equality check never matched and the platform kept its default vanilla name ("Space platform: <default> created in orbit"). Fixed by triggering on any transition *away from* `waiting_for_starter_pack` (that state only ever occurs once, at creation), plus a guard skipping platforms already named `-station`.

## Tips-and-tricks simulations (prototypes/tips-and-tricks-simulations.lua)
- Tip status (`locked`/`unlocked`/`suggested`/etc.) is recorded per-save the first time the game ever sees a given tips-and-tricks-item name. If a save already loaded a tip before `starting_status = "unlocked"` was added to its prototype, the save keeps the old recorded status (usually `locked`) — the new `starting_status` only applies to saves that have truly never seen that tip name. There is no scripting API to reset tip status from control.lua; `/unlock-tips` (console command) is the only way to force-refresh it in an existing save during testing.
- Follow vanilla base-game style for `create_entities_from_blueprint_string`: call it as `surface.create_entities_from_blueprint_string` with the `{ string = ..., position = ... }` table starting on its own line (not inlined after the function name), matching `data/base/prototypes/tips-and-tricks-simulations.lua` (e.g. `simulations.limit_chest`).
- `checkboard = false` (top-level simulation field) disables the fallback checkerboard rendering and is only safe to use when the simulation also has a `save = "...zip"` field with real pre-generated map tiles (e.g. `entering_spaceship_cockpit`). A from-scratch simulation (no `save`, just `game.surfaces[1]`) has no generated tiles at all; setting `checkboard = false` there renders a black void with just the player visible. From-scratch sims should either omit `checkboard` (defaults true) or call `surface.build_checkerboard{...}` explicitly, matching `simulations.spaceship_actions`.
- Rocket silo GUI "Build new space platform" button caption/locale key is `gui-rocket-silo.space-platform-button` (in Factorio's core.cfg). It is NOT gated by any technology — the "space-platform" tech only unlocks recipes (asteroid-collector, crusher, cargo-bay, etc.) *after* the first platform is created via a `research_trigger = {type = "create-space-platform"}`, and its only prerequisite is `rocket-silo` tech.
  - `LuaEntity.use_transitional_requests` maps to the "Automatic requests from space platforms" checkbox, confirmed settable via script (checkbox shows checked after `silo.use_transitional_requests = true`) — BUT per its own docs it's for requesting items "for space platforms in orbit", i.e. resupplying an *existing* platform. It does NOT help create the very first platform (nothing exists yet to request for), so the button stays disabled even with it enabled and empty rocket inventory.
  - Confirmed via in-game `rendering.draw_text` debug label that `surface.planet` CAN be made valid in a simulation via `LuaPlanet.associate_surface(surface)` — but this did NOT fix the greyed-out button either.
  - `LuaForce.is_space_platforms_unlocked()` / `unlock_space_platforms()` / `lock_space_platforms()` also did not fix it.
  - **CRITICAL, CONFIRMED BY ENGINE CRASH LOG**: Actually clicking "Build new space platform" inside a `game.simulation` (tips-and-tricks preview) causes a genuine native SIGSEGV crash in the Factorio engine itself (stack trace: `GameView.cpp: activateNewSpacePlatformGUI` <- `openNewPlatformButtonFromRocketSilo` <- `RocketSiloGui.cpp: newSpacePlatformButtonClicked` <- `LuaSimulation.cpp: luaMouseClick`). This is an engine limitation/bug, NOT a scripting problem — no amount of setup (starter pack, planet association, unlock flags) fixes it, because the actual native GUI flow for creating a platform isn't supported inside the simulation sandbox at all. **Do not ever call `game.simulation.mouse_click()` (or otherwise trigger a click) on the rocket silo's "Build new space platform" button from within a tips-and-tricks simulation** — it will crash the whole Factorio client. If a tip needs to demonstrate this, stop at hovering the button (move_cursor to its widget position) and do not click it.
- `LuaSimulation.control_up{...}` only accepts a `control` key (no `notify`), unlike `control_down`/`control_press` which accept both; passing `notify` to `control_up` errors at runtime.
- `LuaSimulation.move_cursor{position=..., speed=...}` moves the cursor only partway per call and returns whether it will reach the target on this call. For a smooth "slide" it must be invoked from inside a story `condition` function (evaluated every tick) so it's called repeatedly, e.g. `condition = function() return game.simulation.move_cursor{...} end`. Calling it once from a one-shot `action` (tied to a timed `condition`) makes the cursor snap/jump once instead of sliding.
- Always guard entity fields (`entity and entity.valid and entity.position`) before dereferencing, matching the fallback pattern used throughout this file.